      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions fully characterized and matched to COU operating envelope; boundary conditions traceable to calibrated instrumentation with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Experimental flow rates and rotational speeds are reported but inlet turbulence intensity and fluid temperature were not characterized during the hemolysis experiments. Boundary condition uncertainty is partially quantified. Achieved level 3 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metrics (e.g., E%, validation uncertainty Uval) reported for hemolysis index across all 5 operating points; comparison accounts for experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions are compared to experimental measurements at 3 of 5 operating points. Validation uncertainty Uval is not formally computed. Qualitative agreement is reasonable but quantitative metrics are incomplete. Achieved level 3 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation are identical to or directly traceable to the hemolysis index QoI used in the COU submission; no surrogate QoIs accepted at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is used as the primary QoI in both validation and the COU, providing strong relevance. However, the COU requires volume-averaged hemolysis while validation relied on outlet-averaged measurements. Achieved level 4 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
